HEADWORD: Histohæmatin
<hw>His`to*h⟦ae⟧m"a*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"isto`s</grk> tissue + E. <ets>h⟦ae⟧matin</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>One of a class of respiratory pigments,
widely distributed in the animal kingdom, capable of ready oxidation and
reduction.</def>⟦br⟧
